race.comment: TROPICAL SUN (1) just missed in a similar race here two back before being outclassed over 1200m at Belmont where she never really got a chance. Looks better suited back here though and maps for a lovely run. Effort here two back rates highly and she looks the one to beat. COZZIES CHOICE (4) wasn't beaten far in a similar race to this 10 days ago at Northam when 1.9L off the winner. She'll be fitter for that effort and the 3kg claim of Webster comes in handy. Can land in a great spot from the draw and put her best foot forward. STORM LORD (5) won well here two back, beaten TROPICAL SUN, before a 6.3L defeat in a CL3 at Belmont last start. Back to the scene of the crime now and while he has drawn sticky, he's shown he's right up to the mark. Can bounce back. SOLASH MOON (9) will be better for the first-up effort and can improve in what looks an easier race on paper. BILL SELECTS (3) is next best.
